    {
      "id": "title-graph-interface-010",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "🧠 The Graph as Interface",
      "position": {
        "x": -449.90865157832354,
        "y": 240
      },
      "width": 700,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "#9c27b0",
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# 🧠 The Graph as Interface\n\n*A shared reasoning substrate for humans and AI*\n\nThis graph describes a way of working where:\n\n- Thought is **structured**, not buried in chat\n- State is **explicit**, not implicit\n- AI can **read, write, and reason** without taking control\n- Humans remain the source of judgment\n\nThe graph is not a visualization of work.\n\n**It is the interface where work happens.**",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
