    {
      "id": "twilite-why-008",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "❓ Why Use a Twilite Graph?",
      "position": {
        "x": -1180.8242452239183,
        "y": 21.047210308857103
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 360,
      "color": "#2196f3",
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Why Use a Twilite Graph?\n\nA Twilite graph is a **shared reasoning substrate** for humans and AIs.\n\n**For AI:**\n- Read structured state (not just tokens)\n- Write without taking control\n- Reason over relationships\n\n**For humans:**\n- See the structure\n- Render on the web\n- Hold any idea, project, or system\n- Persists across sessions, models, and time\n\n---\n\nText is linear.  \nChats disappear.  \nAgents hide state.\n\nA Twilite graph makes thought **explicit, inspectable, and durable** — without automating judgment.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
            "source": "local",
            "version": ">=0.1.0"
          },
          "views": [
            {
              "key": "markdown",
